Okay, come on.

01:39:28.160 --> 01:39:30.640
Put your arm around me.
Up. Ready?

01:39:31.040 --> 01:39:32.360
Ready?

01:39:32.960 --> 01:39:36.320
Okay, lift. Put your arm around me.
Put your arm around me.

01:39:36.355 --> 01:39:37.600
Good.

01:39:40.640 --> 01:39:43.400
Good. Okay, good.
Here we go. Here we go.

01:39:44.960 --> 01:39:46.240
Okay.

01:39:46.880 --> 01:39:48.160
Okay.

01:39:52.640 --> 01:39:53.920
Okay.

01:39:54.560 --> 01:39:56.445
I need a pill, Ellie.

01:39:56.480 --> 01:39:58.840
It's not time yet. Can you wait?

01:40:00.800 --> 01:40:02.000
No.

01:40:04.640 --> 01:40:06.160
No. Please.

01:40:14.720 --> 01:40:17.120
Oh, I don't wanna live like this.

01:40:24.320 --> 01:40:25.600
Here.

01:40:32.000 --> 01:40:34.080
It'll be better tomorrow.

01:40:39.200 --> 01:40:42.360
No, I won't. This is not living.
This isn't living.

01:40:46.880 --> 01:40:49.280
Why can't...
this be over, baby?

01:40:50.720 --> 01:40:52.960
Please help me.
You help me.

01:40:54.560 --> 01:40:57.960
You're my girl. You help me, please.
Ellie, promise me...

01:40:59.360 --> 01:41:01.040
you'll help me.

01:41:01.760 --> 01:41:03.760
Please. Please. Please.

01:41:06.560 --> 01:41:08.960
We all made this
for you, honey.

01:41:10.400 --> 01:41:13.280
See, it's got our names
all over it, embroidered.

01:41:13.315 --> 01:41:16.120
- Oh, it's beautiful.
- I hope you like it.

01:41:17.120 --> 01:41:20.760
What's that smell? It's that
Indian summer potpourri, isn't it?

01:41:20.960 --> 01:41:23.160
Mm-hmm.
It's your favorite.

01:41:23.840 --> 01:41:26.240
Who's making
a racket out there?

01:41:26.720 --> 01:41:28.640
She brought the baby.

01:41:30.080 --> 01:41:32.520
You girls do good work,
you know?

01:41:33.440 --> 01:41:35.760
Are you available next Tuesday?

01:41:36.320 --> 01:41:39.165
- Oh, here he is.
- He says, "I want Kate".

01:41:39.200 --> 01:41:41.565
- Where's Kate? There she is.
- Oh, I thought I never...

01:41:41.600 --> 01:41:44.960
- Oh, hello, little man. Oh, my gosh.
- Can you sit down for me?

01:41:44.995 --> 01:41:47.320
Oh, gosh.
Who's that cute baby?

01:41:52.640 --> 01:41:54.120
Ellen, I...

01:41:56.480 --> 01:41:59.360
I'm so sorry.
I know it must be very hard...

01:41:59.840 --> 01:42:02.080
for you seeing her like this.

01:42:03.680 --> 01:42:05.160
It's okay.

01:42:06.080 --> 01:42:07.920
It'll be over soon.

01:42:10.880 --> 01:42:12.640
I have a bib too.

01:44:15.600 --> 01:44:17.960
I do remember telling Mrs. Best...

01:44:17.995 --> 01:44:20.320
that it would all be over soon.

01:44:20.880 --> 01:44:22.880
But everyone knew that.

01:44:26.160 --> 01:44:27.560
Ellen...

01:44:28.560 --> 01:44:31.920
did your mother ever ask you
to help her out of her pain?

01:44:31.955 --> 01:44:35.040
Mm-hmm. Yeah, I gave her
her medication every day.

01:44:35.760 --> 01:44:36.960
No.

01:44:39.120 --> 01:44:41.440
Did your mother ever ask you...

01:44:42.000 --> 01:44:44.120
to help her take her life?

01:44:48.240 --> 01:44:52.240
If she did, Ellen, I can say with
some assurance no one in this office...

01:44:53.040 --> 01:44:55.720
I did not help my mother
take her life.

01:44:59.760 --> 01:45:02.520
Where was your father
on that last night?

01:45:03.120 --> 01:45:04.800
He had a class.

01:45:06.000 --> 01:45:09.160
He didn't come home
until she was already sleeping.

01:45:16.080 --> 01:45:17.880
- George.
- Yeah.

01:45:18.480 --> 01:45:20.880
- You came home so early.
- They cancelled my class.

01:45:20.915 --> 01:45:22.080
Oh.

01:45:30.960 --> 01:45:32.840
Hi, you pretty girl.

01:45:34.320 --> 01:45:36.040
Did you miss me?

01:45:36.240 --> 01:45:37.600
Oh, no.

01:45:43.440 --> 01:45:45.680
I want to talk to George now.

01:46:22.320 --> 01:46:24.080
Did you feed her?

01:46:25.200 --> 01:46:27.800
No one should have
to live like that.

01:46:29.040 --> 01:46:30.400
No one.

01:46:30.960 --> 01:46:32.600
Mom said that.

01:46:37.680 --> 01:46:39.320
She was right.

01:47:14.160 --> 01:47:15.400
Hey.

01:47:18.960 --> 01:47:20.880
I finished the table.

01:47:39.120 --> 01:47:40.840
Love you, Ellie.

01:47:45.360 --> 01:47:46.880
I love you.

01:47:51.600 --> 01:47:53.160
I knew that.

01:47:55.440 --> 01:47:57.280
I always knew that.

01:49:39.160 --> 01:49:41.000
Take care, sweetie.

01:49:50.680 --> 01:49:51.880
El?

01:49:53.080 --> 01:49:54.680
- Hey.
- Hi.

01:49:59.320 --> 01:50:00.520
Hi.

01:50:02.680 --> 01:50:04.280
I'm so sorry.

01:50:07.000 --> 01:50:09.280
I don't know what else to say.

01:50:10.360 --> 01:50:11.960
I'm so sorry.

01:50:17.560 --> 01:50:19.120
How are you?

01:50:19.480 --> 01:50:21.160
Yeah. You okay?

01:50:23.320 --> 01:50:26.040
Never knew I could
miss someone so much.

01:50:26.200 --> 01:50:27.600
Oh, God.

01:50:28.120 --> 01:50:30.240
I know.
I missed you too.

01:50:36.760 --> 01:50:39.160
I know this isn't really
a good time to talk, but...

01:50:39.195 --> 01:50:41.525
you know, when you're ready,
we should...

01:50:41.560 --> 01:50:45.240
we should figure out what we're
going to do this year, you know.

01:50:47.320 --> 01:50:49.205
that you just don't understand.

01:50:49.240 --> 01:50:52.440
And I'm sorry, but I don't think
you can understand.

01:50:52.600 --> 01:50:54.700
What? What are you
talking about?

01:50:54.735 --> 01:50:56.800
- Thank you for coming.
- El?

01:52:08.440 --> 01:52:09.840
Ellen...

01:52:10.840 --> 01:52:13.720
your mother died
of an overdose of morphine.

01:52:15.640 --> 01:52:18.800
Can you think of any possible
explanation for that?

01:52:22.360 --> 01:52:26.200
Do you think your father might have
some idea how it might have happened?

01:52:26.235 --> 01:52:28.640
I really don't know
how he could.

01:52:29.080 --> 01:52:32.440
Like I said, he didn't come home
until she was sleeping.

01:52:34.360 --> 01:52:36.280
Have you discussed any of this
with your father?

01:52:36.315 --> 01:52:37.480
No.

01:52:38.200 --> 01:52:41.560
Well, only because I went back
to New York right after the funeral.

01:52:41.595 --> 01:52:43.480
And I really haven't talked
to him since then.

01:52:43.515 --> 01:52:45.840
I've been really busy.
New job.

01:52:47.800 --> 01:52:49.720
- You're writing again?
- Mm-hmm.

01:52:49.755 --> 01:52:51.960
Feature writer for the Voice.

01:52:52.720 --> 01:52:54.720
Hmph.
Congratulations.

01:52:56.440 --> 01:52:57.800
Thanks.

01:53:01.240 --> 01:53:03.720
I may want to speak to your father.

01:53:06.520 --> 01:53:07.960
Anyway...

01:53:08.440 --> 01:53:09.920
thank you.

01:53:10.840 --> 01:53:12.120
Sure.

01:53:19.000 --> 01:53:20.920
I'm sorry for your loss.

01:53:20.955 --> 01:53:22.400
Thank you.

01:54:03.640 --> 01:54:05.840
How long have you been here?

01:54:06.040 --> 01:54:07.480
Not long.

01:54:10.360 --> 01:54:13.760
I can smell the lilacs
and the hollyhocks under the soil.

01:54:17.560 --> 01:54:20.760
Your mother used to say
she could do the same thing.

01:54:23.800 --> 01:54:25.600
How'd it go today?

01:54:25.720 --> 01:54:27.560
All right, I guess.

01:54:28.600 --> 01:54:31.120
He's gonna want
to talk to you too.

01:54:33.880 --> 01:54:37.480
Ellen, I just want you to know
how much I admire your courage.

01:54:38.200 --> 01:54:40.200
And I wish I'd done it.

01:54:42.520 --> 01:54:43.800
What?

01:54:44.920 --> 01:54:46.520
I wish I had.

01:54:50.680 --> 01:54:52.200
I would've.

01:54:55.960 --> 01:54:57.400
Couldn't.

01:55:05.080 --> 01:55:06.960
Dad, I didn't do it.

01:55:07.960 --> 01:55:10.360
I didn't do it.
I thought that...

01:55:11.800 --> 01:55:14.560
All this time,
I thought that it was you.

01:55:21.040 --> 01:55:22.920
- Oh, my God.
- No.

01:55:24.280 --> 01:55:26.680
- It's impossible.
- Oh, my God.

01:55:27.160 --> 01:55:29.880
She was too helpless.
She was too frail.

01:55:38.200 --> 01:55:39.680
The pills.

01:55:40.120 --> 01:55:42.080
How could sh...? Jesus.

01:55:48.760 --> 01:55:50.240
Ellen, I...

01:55:52.600 --> 01:55:54.440
I love your mother.

01:56:04.600 --> 01:56:07.720
I don't suppose
I'm ever going to stop loving her.

01:56:12.760 --> 01:56:15.200
But because she can do anything...

01:56:16.600 --> 01:56:18.920
run the house, run our lives...

01:56:19.000 --> 01:56:21.840
keep everything
so beautiful and so warm...

01:56:29.080 --> 01:56:31.760
I only thought
of what she meant to me.

01:56:31.960 --> 01:56:33.480
My... muse.

01:56:37.240 --> 01:56:39.040
My... lovely wife.

01:56:43.000 --> 01:56:44.800
My one true thing.

01:56:49.240 --> 01:56:51.160
Of course she did it.

01:56:52.120 --> 01:56:54.640
Who else would've had
the strength?

01:57:21.880 --> 01:57:24.440
No, you have to go
deeper than that.

01:57:24.760 --> 01:57:26.920
You have to go four inches.

01:57:29.080 --> 01:57:30.800
- Four?
- Yeah.

01:57:32.920 --> 01:57:36.280
Yeah, so that they don't rot in the snow,
or so that the animals don't get them.

01:57:36.315 --> 01:57:37.640
Uh-huh.

01:57:38.200 --> 01:57:41.720
And then four inches apart
so that the roots don't tangle...

01:57:42.520 --> 01:57:44.880
and they'll just
look prettier.

01:57:48.280 --> 01:57:50.240
What are these plants?

01:57:50.680 --> 01:57:52.160
Daffodils.

01:57:52.600 --> 01:57:54.920
- These are daffodils?
- Yeah.

